{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:27:56.822Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Component Structure**\n\nI've made good progress! I've confirmed `PrivatePageHeader` is indeed well-structured. I'm now looking closely at `WorkspaceCard` and other components, which I found in `components/private-app/cards-metrics-badges.tsx` as we discovered. I'm currently focused on ensuring the new file covers all required views and data points, starting with the \"clients overview\".\n\n\n**Planning Bento Layout**\n\nI'm now deep in planning the bento layout. I'm aiming for a dense yet elegant presentation using a 12-column grid. The plan involves a grid-based approach with metric tiles on the first row, followed by a main bento grid spanning the next two rows. I've started mapping out potential content, like active projects, AI operations overview, pending support tickets, billing status, and governance alerts. I'm considering MetricTile usage, and trying to decide what should be included, such as active sandboxes, system load, SLA uptime transitions and compliance level, as well as a focus on the clients overview.\n\n\n**Defining Bento Content**\n\nI've been defining the content for the bento layout. I'm focusing on the specifics for each tile. I am including client overview with Name, Domain, Tier, Compliance Score, Status, and an action button. Next up is active projects, a high-density table from `previewProjects` showing Project Name, Isolation Mode, Active Node Count, and Status. I'm also thinking about AI operations overview from `previewAgentOperations` and governance alerts with active rule checks from `previewGovernanceItems`, and pending support tickets.\n\n\n**Designing Command Actions**\n\nI'm now designing interactive command actions. I'm prioritizing Critical/High SLA tickets, including an SLA timer countdown or live badge. Also, I'm thinking about an interactive quick reply button. I'm also now designing a financial ledger bento block spanning multiple columns and summarizing invoices with statuses, cryptographic signatures, and a billing summary. Command actions at the top of the dashboard or inside each bento block, such as a Force Core HSM Rotation, are under consideration.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Actions**\n\nI'm now implementing interactive command actions with React hooks. I've got a plan for state management, including terminal logs, an enclave node counter, a client filter, and support tickets. I'm focusing on \"Trigger Compliance Audit Scan\", \"Mute Non-Critical Telemetry Alerts\", and \"Provision Transient Enclave Node\".\n\n\n**Refining Ticket Filters**\n\nI'm refining the ticket filters. I'm adding toggles for \"Open\", \"In Progress\", and \"Resolved\" statuses. I'm also thinking about adding a toggle to \"Acknowledge Alerts\" which updates the governance items' status in local state, which looks promising.\n\n\n"}}
